  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Accounts Assistant",
  "description": "<p><strong>Responsibilities:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Performing system entries for all Accounts Receivable (AR) sales &amp; payment received transactions</li>\n  <li>Work closely with Customer Service and Sales team to investigate and resolve billing disputes, discrepancies relating to outstanding invoices</li>\n  <li>Generate monthly statement of accounts and update AR aging report on a monthly basis</li>\n  <li>Performing system entries for Accounts Payables (AP) purchase and expenses transactions including payment processing matters</li>\n  <li>Ensure proper and systematic filling is done in a timely and accurate manner</li>\n  <li>Assist to perform quarterly GST submission and other statutory reporting</li>\n  <li>Perform other ad-hoc duties as assigned</li>\n</ul>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><strong>Requirements:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Minimum LCCI/CAT or Diploma in Accounting</li>\n  <li>Minimum 1 year of relevant working experience in a similar role</li>\n  <li>Meticulous, pro-active and with good organization skills</li>\n  <li>Proficiency in Microsoft Office (Word/Excel/PowerPoint)</li>\n  <li>Experienced in usage of any ERP system will be added advantage</li>\n  <li>Those with simple full set accounts or willing to learn will be an advantage as well</li>\n  <li>Ability to work in a fast-paced environment and meet timelines</li>\n  <li>Ability to liaise with Chinese speaking customer fluently</li>\n</ul>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><strong>What we offer:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Attractive remuneration package depending on qualification and working experience</li>\n  <li>Annual leave, medical welfare and insurance</li>\n  <li>5-day work week (Monday to Friday: 9am to 6pm)</li>\n</ul>",
